1. Open Source License – GNU Affero General Public License v3.0
   (AGPL-3.0-only)

This project is licensed under the GNU Affero General Public License
version 3.0 (AGPL-3.0-only).

You may use, study, modify, and self-host this software free of charge,
including for private, educational, and experimental purposes, provided
that you comply with the terms of the AGPL.

In particular
- If you modify the software and make it available to users over a network,
  you must also make the complete corresponding source code available
  under the same license.
- All derivative works must remain licensed under the AGPL.

The full license text can be found in the file
  LICENSE-AGPL.txt

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

2. Commercial License

A separate commercial license is required if you intend to use this
software in a way that is not compatible with the AGPL, including but not
limited to

- Offering the software or a modified version as a hosted or managed
  service (SaaS) without fulfilling AGPL source code disclosure
  obligations
- Integrating the software into proprietary or closed-source products
- Using the software as part of a commercial offering where source code
  disclosure is not desired

Commercial licensing allows proprietary use without AGPL obligations.

For commercial licensing inquiries, please contact the project owner.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

Intent and Philosophy
---------------------

MatrosDMS is published openly to encourage learning, experimentation,
discussion, and collaboration. The AGPL is used to ensure that improvements
to the software—especially in networked environments—remain accessible
to the community.

The commercial license exists to enable sustainable development and to
support use cases where open-source reciprocity is not feasible.

This project is not positioned as a drop-in enterprise product, but as a
transparent and opinionated technology study.

